quran[13]{c,v,t}:
  28,76,"Indeed, Korah¬†was from the people of Moses, but he behaved arrogantly towards them. We had granted him such treasures that even their keys would burden a group of strong men. ňĻSome ofňļ his people advised him, ‚ÄúDo not be prideful! Surely God does not like the prideful"
  28,77,"Rather, seek the ňĻrewardňļ of the Hereafter by means of what God has granted you, without forgetting your share of this world. And be good ňĻto othersňļ as God has been good to you. Do not seek to spread corruption in the land, for God certainly does not like the corruptors.‚ÄĚ"
  28,78,"He replied, ‚ÄúI have been granted all this because of some knowledge I have.‚ÄĚ¬†Did he not know that God had already destroyed some from the generations before him who were far superior to him in power and greater in accumulating ňĻwealthňļ? There will be no need for the wicked to be asked about their sins"
  28,79,"Then he came out before his people in all his glamour. Those who desired the life of this world wished, ‚ÄúIf only we could have something like what Korah has been given. He is truly a man of great fortune!‚ÄĚ"
  28,80,"But those gifted with knowledge said, ‚ÄúShame on you! God‚Äôs reward is far better for those who believe and do good. But none will attain this except the steadfast.‚ÄĚ"
  28,81,"Then We caused the earth to swallow him up, along with his home. There was no one to help him against God, nor could he even help himself"
  28,82,"And those who had craved his position the previous day began to say, ‚ÄúAh! It is certainly God Who gives abundant or limited provisions to whoever He wills of His servants. Had it not been for the grace of God, He could have surely caused the earth to swallow us up! Oh, indeed! The disbelievers will never succeed.‚ÄĚ"
  28,83,That ňĻeternalňļ Home in the Hereafter We reserve ňĻonlyňļ for those who seek neither tyranny nor corruption on the earth. The ultimate outcome belongs ňĻonlyňļ to the righteous
  28,84,"Whoever comes with a good deed will be rewarded with what is better. And whoever comes with an evil deed, then the evildoers will only be rewarded for what they used to do"
  28,85,"Most certainly, the One Who has ordained the Quran for you will ňĻultimatelyňļ bring you back home ňĻto Meccaňļ.¬†Say, ‚ÄúMy Lord knows best who has come with ňĻtrueňļ guidance and who is clearly astray.‚ÄĚ"
  28,86,"You never expected this Book to be revealed to you, but ňĻit cameňļ only ňĻasňļ a mercy from your Lord. So never side with the disbelievers ňĻin their disbeliefňļ"
  28,87,"Do not let them turn you away from the revelations of God after they have been sent down to you. Rather, invite ňĻallňļ to ňĻthe Way ofňļ your Lord, and never be one of the polytheists"
  28,88,And do not invoke any other god with God. There is no god ňĻworthy of worshipňļ except Him. Everything is bound to perish except He Himself.¬†All authority belongs to Him. And to Him you will ňĻallňļ be returned